# SVN vs Git

| Feature | SVN | Git |
|---------|-----|-----|
| Type | Centralized | Distributed |
| Repository | Central Server | Local + Remote |
| Internet Required | Usually Yes | No (for most operations) |
| Offline Work | Limited | Fully Supported |
| Speed | Slower | Faster |
| Backup | Server Only | Every Developer Has a Copy |
| Branching | Slower | Very Fast |
| Merging | More Difficult | Easier |
| Failure Risk | High (Server Failure) | Low |
| Popularity | Moderate | Very High |

---

# Centralized vs Distributed

| Feature | Centralized VCS | Distributed VCS |
|----------|-----------------|-----------------|
| Project History | Stored on Server | Stored on Every Computer |
| Offline Work | Limited | Excellent |
| Collaboration | Good | Excellent |
| Speed | Moderate | Fast |
| Backup | Single Backup | Multiple Backups |
| Failure Risk | High | Low |
| Internet Dependency | High | Low |
| Branching | Slower | Faster |
| Merging | More Complex | Easier |
| Examples | SVN, CVS | Git, Mercurial |

